The paper deals with the problem of information dissemination in networks with latencies, which is a topic in distributed systems (cs.DS) and networked systems (cs.NI). The concept of weighted conductance and critical latency is introduced, which falls under the category of graph theory and algorithms (cs.DS, cs.SI). The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem and gives algorithms for solving it, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY).
